Subject:    Remaining Domain Problems
From:       <a href="?a=90366379700014&r=1&w=2">lazear () gateway ! mitre ! org</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198707">1987-07-31 13:10:06</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781926906&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781926906&q=raw">body</a>]</b>


In conjunction with the dissolution of the IETF working group on
domains and Doug Kingston's job change, it seems appropriate to
try to evaluate the status of the domain system.  This could be
used as the basis for further work or the recognition that there
is little or none to be done.

I am soliciting your thoughts on what the top 4-5 problems are
that still exist relative to the domain system.  These could be
a favorite enhancement you think is useful/necessary or a real
operational problem that still lingers.  Especially interesting
would be any MILNET problems you see in place or about to occur
as a result of the ongoing ad hoc transition.

I will summarize all ideas back to the lists.

	Walt Lazear

